            <title>[LU-7729] Don&apos;t return ptlrpc_error() in process_req_last_xid().</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7729</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;process_req_last_xid():&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;               &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!(lustre_msg_get_flags(req-&amp;gt;rq_reqmsg) &amp;amp; MSG_REPLAY)) {
                       req-&amp;gt;rq_status = -EPROTO;
                       RETURN(ptlrpc_error(req));
               }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will return 0 to caller mistakenly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
